# Pug + Tailwind Variant Class Safety

- In `template lang="pug"`, do **not** use dot-shorthand when a class contains `:` (like `md:`, `sm:`, `hover:`).
- Dot-shorthand is only safe for plain class names without special characters.
- For Tailwind variant classes, always use `class="..."` (or `:class="..."`) on the element.

```pug
// ❌ BAD (Pug parse error)
.grid.grid-cols-1.md:grid-cols-3.gap-3

// ✅ GOOD
div(class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-3")

// ✅ GOOD (mixed)
.grid.gap-3(class="grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3")
```

- Before finishing a Vue/Pug edit, quickly scan for `.[^\\s]*:` patterns and rewrite them to `class="..."`.
